.TH "vmw_stdu_primary_plane_prepare_fb" 9 "vmw_stdu_primary_plane_prepare_fb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_stdu_primary_plane_prepare_fb \- Readies the display surface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_stdu_primary_plane_prepare_fb
.BI "(struct drm_plane *plane "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane_state *new_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "plane" 12
display plane
.IP "new_state" 12
info on the new plane state, including the FB
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates a new display surface if the content is
backed by a buffer object.  The display surface is pinned here, and it'll
be unpinned in .\fBcleanup_fb\fP

Returns 0 on success
